Johnny Bothwell (May 23, 1917 in Ross Township, Gary, Lake County,, Indiana – September 12, 1995 in Lakeland, Florida) was an American jazz alto saxophonist and bandleader.
Bothwell played in Chicago in 1940 and then moved to New York City, playing with Woody Herman (1943) and Sonny Dunham (1944–46).
